# Client safety (90-day human-in-the-loop)

## Before starting work

- Confirm the request is scoped. If unclear, ask one focused question in the Slack thread.
- Do not start implementation until Mennt has triaged or the client has approved an estimate.
- Never merge PRs. Mennt humans merge after review.

## Scope limits

- Keep diffs small and focused on the stated request.
- Do not add new dependencies without explicit approval in the thread.
- Do not modify auth, billing, infrastructure, or database schemas without Mennt human approval.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.

## Output

- Slack threads: Slack mrkdwn (`*bold*`, `•` bullets). **No tables or `|` pipe rows.**
- End every client-facing reply with what was done and what needs Mennt review.
- If opening a PR, note that it is a draft awaiting Mennt merge.
- Never expose secrets, tokens, or internal Mennt systems in Slack replies.
